definitions.definition: Of or pertaining to the female gender ; womanly .
Of or pertaining to the female sex ; biologically female, not male.
Belonging to females; typically used by females.
examples: Mary, Elizabeth, and Edith are feminine names.

definitions.definition: Having the qualities stereotypically associated with women : nurturing , not aggressive .
Of, pertaining or belonging to the female grammatical gender , in languages that have gender distinctions.

subdefinitions.definition: Being of the feminine class or grammatical gender, and inflected in that manner.
Being inflected in agreement with a feminine noun.

definitions.definition: Having the vowel harmony of a front vowel .
definitions.label_groups: grammar , Mongolic languages , of any word

definitions.definition: Following or ending on an unstressed syllable.
examples: Feminine caesura , feminine catalexis , feminine ending , feminine rhyme .
